ommons/commons-fileupload2-core/2.0.0-M5/reachability-metadata.json`. This looks more like a workflow/orchestration failure after the javac fix than a still-broken test.\n\nPlease inspect:\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.commons:commons-fileupload2-core:2.0.0-M5/fix-javac-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-01T17-33-37-062352Z.log`\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.commons:commons-fileupload2-core:2.0.0-M5/fix-javac-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-01T13-30-58-718144Z.log`\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.commons:commons-fileupload2-core:2.0.0-M5/populate-artifact-urls/populate_artifact_urls.log`\n\nNext steps:\n1. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.commons:commons-fileupload2-core:2.0.0-M5` on a clean worktree to confirm the recovered test still passes.\n2. Re-run `./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=org.apache.commons:commons-fileupload2-core:2.0.0-M5` and verify why the transient automation worktree reported a missing `reachability-metadata.json`.\n3. If both pass, treat this as a stale/spurious workflow failure and close or retrigger the issue instead of making a new manual code fix."}}
